radiographic_examinations.findings: Small mobile gallstones identified within a mildly distended gallbladder; small amount of pericholecystic fluid without wall edema; no intrahepatic biliary dilation; hepatic parenchyma appears within normal limits; no focal liver mass; the main portal vein is patent; no ascites; imaged portion of pancreas appears within normal limits; no masses or pancreatic ductal dilation; no masses, hydronephrosis, or stones in kidneys.
